# TanStack Query v5

Used for client-side data fetching in `apps/web`. Pair with tRPC when calling backend procedures.

## Provider

- Create one `QueryClient` per browser session via `useState(() => new QueryClient(...))` inside a `"use client"` provider.
- Set sensible defaults: `refetchOnWindowFocus: false`, `retry: 1` (already configured in `WeddingQueryProvider`).

## Query Keys

- Keys are arrays starting with a feature namespace: `["wedding", "guestbook"]`, `["wedding", "guestbook", { id }]`.
- Centralize keys in a `queryKeys.ts` module when they grow; avoid stringly-typed keys scattered across files.

## v5 API Changes (vs v4)

```ts
// ❌ REMOVED: callbacks on useQuery
useQuery({ queryKey, queryFn, onSuccess, onError }); // ❌ no longer exists

// ✅ Handle results from returned data/error
const { data, error, isPending, isError } = useQuery({ queryKey, queryFn });
useEffect(() => { if (error) toast.error(...); }, [error]);
```

- `isLoading` → use **`isPending`** for "no data yet" and `isFetching` for "any in-flight".
- `cacheTime` → renamed **`gcTime`**.
- Single signature: hooks now take exactly one object argument.
- `useMutation` **still has `onSuccess` / `onError` / `onSettled`** — use those for side effects on writes.

## Mutations

```ts
const create = useMutation({
  mutationFn: createGuestbookEntryRequest,
  onSuccess: (entry) => {
    queryClient.setQueryData<GuestbookEntry[]>(
      ["wedding", "guestbook"],
      (prev) => [entry, ...(prev ?? [])],
    );
  },
});
create.mutate(input); // or await create.mutateAsync(input)
```

- Prefer `queryClient.setQueryData` for optimistic insert/update; fall back to `invalidateQueries` when in doubt.
- Use `mutation.isPending` (not `isLoading`) for the submit-in-flight state.

## Suspense / SSR

- Use `useSuspenseQuery` to read data with Suspense boundaries.
- For SSR/RSC handoff, prefetch on the server via `queryClient.prefetchQuery` and pass `dehydrate(queryClient)` to a `<HydrationBoundary>` on the client.

## Rules

- Do NOT use `useEffect` + `fetch` for data fetching in client components — use `useQuery` or a tRPC hook.
- Always pass an `AbortSignal` from `queryFn` context to underlying fetches when supported.
- Co-locate query/mutation hooks with their feature in `src/features/<feature>/hooks/`.
- Never instantiate a new `QueryClient` inside a render body — wrap with `useState` or a module-level singleton on the server.
